                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.61351/3908a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-28T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 28, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>624. From Brown,<note n="91" xml:id="d156fn91">Courtney Brown, vice president of
                        the Commodity Credit Corporation.</note> CCC. You are requested to make a
                    firm offer to the Cuban Sugar Stabilization Institute for the 300,000 tons of
                    free sugar produced in Cuba during the 1943 crop,<note n="92" xml:id="d156fn92"
                        >The Purchase Agreement on the 1943 sugar crop authorized the production of
                        300,000 short tons of raw sugar for sale in world markets, and granted to
                        Commodity Credit Corporation an option on its purchase.</note> under the
                    same terms as governed the purchase of the 2,700,000 tons. If accepted you are
                    authorized to exchange letters immediately so that June first payment can
                    include this sugar, providing that the Institute can issue proper identity
                    certificates by that date. [Brown.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
